<dl id="n12138p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12138p">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12138p"> 138(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ pyramid</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Third Dynasty begins the Pyramid Age <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Zoser built a mastaba with a burial chamber <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> He then made a stone mastaba, eighty feet high, two hundred and twenty feet wide, and an uncertain amount longer from north to south. As time went on he built five others on top, each smaller than its predecessor, producing a terraced structure one hundred and ninety feet high, in six stages, like the Babylonian ziggurat or stepped <mark>pyramid</mark>. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 34-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
